Cape Town Two groups of alleged gangsters are expected to appear in court on charges of public violence, following a clash between them outside the Strand Magistrate s Court on Thursday, which left a man bleeding inside the building, from a stab wound, and two windows damaged. The two groups, one consisting of eight men and the other more, were rounded up by police soon after the alleged incident, and are currently in custody. They are expected back in court on Friday. An attorney described the scene as chaotic . An official said the alleged incident started with shouting outside the building, and when another official went out of the building in an attempt to restore order, a woman outside shouted to the official: Be careful, that man has a gun. The official retreated back into the building, and locked the doors to find a wounded man lying on the floor inside the building bleeding from his wrist. African News Agency